JOHANNESBURG – The chairperson of Transnet’s board, Linda Mabaso, has resigned. The Public Enterprises Department says it’s also received the resignations of non-executive directors Vusi Nkonyane and Yasmin Forbes. READ: Transnet CFO Garry Pita resigns The resignations come a day before the parastatal is scheduled to hold a shareholder’s meeting. Gordhan: SA to recover money stolen from state companies Earlier this week, Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan proposed to parliament, that lifestyle audits be conducted for state-owned enterprises executives. The department says all allegations of corruption and state capture will be fully investigated. New appointments will be announced soon. eNCA